FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $80,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since April 21 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWIST (FR) stalked the pace from inside, took over at the five-sixteenths pole, quickly cleared then started to lug out with a quarter mile remaining, continued to lug out in the stretch but was able to hold safely in the end. YES THIS TIME brushed leaving the gate, unhurried in the early going and moved inside, gained along the fence through the far turn, tipped out in the lane, closed determinedly but could not reach the winner. CROSBY BEACH got bumped on both sides and crowded at the start, steered to the inside racing near the back, went two to three wide on the far turn, tipped out then altered back inward in upper stretch, showed a mild response and gained the show honors. FLASHIEST raced off the rail then outside a rival towards the rear on the clubhouse turn, went four deep into the second bend, spun six wide into the lane and got outfinished for third. SEVEN CHARMS brushed with inner rival at the start, angled to the inside while off the pace, moved into range leaving the backstretch, asked around the far turn and flattened in the furlong grounds. LURE HIM IN raced in mid-pack a bit off the rail, took closer order between in the middle stages, chased two wide into the lane and lacked a bid. DON'T SWEAR DAVE stalked off the rail, went three deep into the far turn, got shuffled back and angled in, then failed to find the needed response in the drive. BALLADEER dueled from outside leaving the chute then ceded command to the pacesetter, stalked outside a rival up the backstretch, got floated out by ASTRONOMER at the three-eighths pole, traveled four to five leaving that bend and failed to produce a bid. MAJESTIC EAGLE chased widest into the stretch for the first time, went four wide around the clubhouse turn, lost positions in the middle stages, had to alter course when TESORO was taken out wide at the three-eighths pole, cut the corner into the stretch and failed to menace. ASTRONOMER bumped with outer rival leaving the gate, went up to duel from inside then cleared, showed the way to the far turn, drifted out at the three-eighths pole, gave up command shortly after and retreated through the drive. TESORO brushed at the start, allowed to settle three deep, eased out of the race at the three-eighths pole, stopped at the furlong marker and walked off.
